# ช้าช้าไทย — Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.local for local development
# Set in: Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables

# ── Supabase (Singapore region: ap-southeast-1) ────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...your-anon-key...

# ── Supabase mode ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to "true" for production, "false" to fall back to window.storage (dev only)
VITE_USE_SUPABASE=true

# ── AI Provider Keys (SERVER-SIDE — not exposed to client) ──────────────────
# These are read by the /api/ai-enrich serverless function.
# Set them once here and the app works out-of-the-box — no need for each
# teacher to configure their own keys in Settings.
#
# The app uses a 3-provider fallback chain:
#   1. Google Gemini 2.5 Flash  (primary, best Thai support)
#   2. Groq Llama 3.3 70B       (1st fallback, OpenAI-compatible)
#   3. Cloudflare Workers AI    (2nd fallback, Llama 3.3 70B)
#
# If a provider has no key, it is skipped automatically.
# If a provider fails (quota, network, etc.), the next one is tried.
# Teachers can still add personal keys in Settings to override the server defaults.
#
# Where to get free keys (no credit card needed):
#   Google Gemini:    aistudio.google.com → Get API key
#   Groq:             console.groq.com → API Keys
#   Cloudflare:       dash.cloudflare.com → Account ID (sidebar) +
#                     My Profile → API Tokens → Workers AI template
#
# ── Notes ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_ prefixed vars are embedded in the client bundle (visible to users).
# Non-prefixed vars (GEMINI_API_KEY, etc.) are server-only — safe for secrets.
# After setting these in Cloudflare Pages, trigger a new deployment.

# ── GitHub Issue Auto-Reporting (SERVER-SIDE) ──────────────────────────────
# Used by /api/report-error to create GitHub issues when the client-side
# ErrorBoundary catches a crash. Optional — if not set, errors are only
# logged to the browser console.
#
# Create a fine-grained PAT at: github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens
# Permissions: Contents (read) + Issues (write) on the repo
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_fine_grained_pat
GITHUB_REPO_OWNER=brunodias-a11y
GITHUB_REPO_NAME=chaachaathai

# ── Google Drive Backup (SERVER-SIDE) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Used by /api/drive-oauth-start, /api/drive-oauth-callback (#368) and, once
# built, /api/drive-backup (#369) — periodic word-bank backup to the
# teacher's own Google Drive (#58).
#
# Setup (Google Cloud Console — see issue #367 for the full walkthrough):
#   1. Create/reuse a project, enable the "Google Drive API"
#   2. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
#   3. Authorized redirect URI: <your production domain>/api/drive-oauth-callback
#      must match GOOGLE_DRIVE_REDIRECT_URI below EXACTLY (including https://)
#   4. Scope used: drive.file only (the app only sees files it creates itself,
#      under a "Chaa Chaa Thai Backups/" folder) — avoids Google's sensitive-
#      scope verification process required for full Drive access.
GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-your-client-secret
GOOGLE_DRIVE_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-production-domain/api/drive-oauth-callback

# Where /api/drive-oauth-callback sends the browser back to after the Google
# consent flow finishes (success, denied, or error) — same production domain
# as above, no path.
APP_BASE_URL=https://your-production-domain

# Protects /api/drive-backup (#369) — this endpoint refreshes access tokens
# and writes to every connected teacher's Drive in one shot, so it must not
# be triggerable by anyone who just finds the URL. Any random string you
# choose — kept separate from WEEKLY_REPORT_SECRET on purpose (least
# privilege: a leaked report secret shouldn't also be able to trigger Drive
# writes). Required as the `X-Backup-Secret` request header.
DRIVE_BACKUP_SECRET=choose-a-different-random-string

# Shared with /api/weekly-report (#334) and /api/send-weekly-report (#335) —
# this repo's .env.example never actually had it documented despite being in
# use since then, fixing that here too. Supabase dashboard -> Settings ->
# API -> service_role key (secret, bypasses RLS — needed because these
# Functions read/write data for teachers other than whoever is "logged in").
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...your-service-role-key...

# Also used by /api/weekly-report and /api/send-weekly-report (#334/#335) as
# the required `X-Report-Secret` header — any random string you choose,
# undocumented here until now for the same reason as above.
WEEKLY_REPORT_SECRET=choose-any-random-string

# ── Push Notifications (Web Push / VAPID) (#573) ────────────────────────────
# Generate a key pair once with: npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
# Public key → set here (exposed to client, safe)
# Private key → set as Edge Function secret in Supabase dashboard (never commit)
VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=your-vapid-public-key-here
